commands.name: az resource-mover move-resource add
commands.summary: Create a Move Resource in the move collection.
commands.syntax:
az resource-mover move-resource add [--depends-on-overrides]
                                    [--existing-target-id]
                                    [--ids]
                                    [--move-collection-name]
                                    [--move-resource-name]
                                    [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                    [--resource-group]
                                    [--resource-settings]
                                    [--source-id]
                                    [--subscription]
examples: az resource-mover move-resource add --resource-group MyResourceGroup --move-collection-name MyMoveCollection --name MoveResourceName --source-id "/subscriptions/subID/resourceGroups/myRG/providers/Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/MyVNet" --resource-settings '{ "resourceType": "Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks", "targetResourceName": "MyVNet-target" }'

az resource-mover move-resource add --resource-group MyResourceGroup --move-collection-name MyZonalMoveCollection --name MyVMMoveResource --source-id "/subscriptions/subID/resourceGroups/MyResourceGroup/providers/Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/MyVM" --resource-settings '{ "resourceType": "Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines", "targetResourceName": "MyVM", "targetAvailabilityZone": "2", "targetVmSize": "Standard_B2s" }'

az resource-mover move-resource add --resource-group MyResourceGroup --move-collection-name MyMoveCollection --name MoveResourceName --source-id "/subscriptions/subID/resourceGroups/eastusRG/providers/Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/MyVM" --depends-on-overrides id="/subscriptions/subID/resourceGroups/eastusRG/providers/Microsoft.Network/networkInterfaces/MyNIC" target-id="/subscriptions/subID/resourceGroups/westusRG/providers/Microsoft.Network/networkInterfaces/MyNIC" --resource-settings '{ "resourceType": "Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines", "targetAvailabilitySetId": "/subscriptions/subID/resourceGroups/eastusRG/providers/Microsoft.Compute/availabilitySets/MyAVSet", "targetAvailabilityZone": "2", "targetResourceName": "MyVM-target", "targetVmSize": null, "userManagedIdentities": [/subscriptions/subid/resourceGroups/eastusRG/providers/Microsoft.ManagedIdentity/userAssignedIdentities/umi1] }'

commands.name: az resource-mover move-resource delete
commands.summary: Delete a Move Resource from the move collection.
commands.syntax:
az resource-mover move-resource delete [--ids]
                                       [--move-collection-name]
                                       [--move-resource-name]
                                       [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                       [--resource-group]
                                       [--subscription]
                                       [--yes]
examples: az resource-mover move-resource delete --move-collection-name MyMoveCollection --name MyMoveResource --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az resource-mover move-resource list
commands.summary: List the Move Resources in the move collection.
examples: az resource-mover move-resource list --move-collection-name MyMoveCollection --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az resource-mover move-resource show
examples: az resource-mover move-resource show --move-collection-name MyMoveCollection --name MyMoveResource --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az resource-mover move-resource wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
